/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  column06_fullMESH / constant/thermoPackage

  benzene (light) / toluene (heavy): the same near-ideal aromatic pair as
  column01, kept deliberately identical --- Raoult + ideal gas at ~1 atm ---
  so any difference in the answer could only come from the numerics.  The
  point of the case is the simultaneous MESH Newton solver, validated
  against the bubble-point solution on thermodynamics that are beyond doubt.
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

components       ( benzene  toluene );

activityModel    { model  ideal; }
equationOfState  { model  idealGas; }
